result.execSummary:
The defendant Sarah A Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Sarah A Johnson is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Sarah A Johnson was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Sarah A Johnson was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Repeater], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

records.addlTxt: Cases heard: 13CF145, 13CF320, 14CF128 & 14CF129, Defendant Sarah A Johnson in court, in custody with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Christine M. Genda appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court sentenced defendant in 13CF145 to 9 months jail on each count, concurrent with each other. (207 days jail credit) Civil judgment entered for unpaid costs. In 13CF320, sentence on ct. 1 to 4 yrs. prison, consisting of 2 yr. confinement, 2 yr. extended supervision, concurrent with 13CF145, on ct. 3 to 1 yr. confinement, 1 1/2 yr. extended supervision, concurrent with ct. 1 & 13CF145 Defendant is eligible for Earned Early Release and Substance Abuse Program. (244 days jail credit) Civil judgment entered for unpaid costs. In 14CF128, Defendant plead no contest to cts. 2&3. Court found defendant guilty, sentenced defendant on each count to 2 yr. prison, consisting of 1 yr. confinement and 1 yr. extended supervision. Counts are concurrent with each other, but consecutive to 13CCF145 & 13CF320.  $543 costs on each ct. Ct. 1 dismissed. Defendant is eligible for Earned Early Release and Substance Abuse Program. No jail credit. Conditions of Extended Supervision on both prison cases: Psychological evaluation and comply with recommendations, complete AODA, comply with treatment, successfully complete aggression/anger management counseling, no contact with J.S. except for child related issues or upon agents approval. 14CF129 dismissed.

Defendant Sarah A Johnson in court, in custody with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Brenda L. Yaskal appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Cases called: 14CF128 and 14CF129.  Defendant stood mute. Court entered not guilty plea, jury trial to be set. Bond continued.

Defendant Sarah A Johnson in court, in custody with attorney Mark D. Lawton.  Jane E. Kohlwey appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Waiver of Right to Prelim filed, Court accepts Waiver, probable cause found, bound over for further proceedings,  Arraignment scheduled for August 29, 2014 at 02:45 pm.

Defendant Sarah A Johnson in court with attorney Roger L Klopp.  Jane E Kohlwey appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has requested a new atty from public defenders office.  New dates set.  Bond remains.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 20, 2014 at 10:10 am.  Hearing scheduled for July 9, 2014 at 02:45 pm.
